\n\n## Core Types\n\n```rust\npub(crate) struct CaptureRequest {\n    // Must come from existing `but -C` / CLI repository resolution. Transcript\n    // `cwd` is validation-only and must not select the repository.\n    pub(crate) repo_path: PathBuf,\n    pub(crate) agent: String,\n    // Required for the POC. Optional later once session discovery exists.\n    pub(crate) transcript_path: PathBuf,\n    pub(crate) target: Option<String>,\n    pub(crate) dry_run: bool,\n}\n\npub(crate) struct CaptureReport {\n    pub(crate) target: String,\n    pub(crate) records_new: usize,\n    pub(crate) transcript_records_appended: usize,\n    pub(crate) dry_run: bool,\n}\n\npub struct CommandOutput {\n    message: String,\n}\n```\n\nOnly the CLI command and `CommandOutput` are public crate surface for the POC.\n`CommandOutput` serializes as `{ \"message\": \"...\" }`; richer reporting stays\ninternal unless it becomes useful.\n\n## Capture Pipeline\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[\"CLI command\"] --> B[\"Build CaptureRequest\"]\n    B --> C[\"Resolve repository\"]\n    C --> D[\"Resolve target\"]\n    D --> E[\"Select agent collector\"]\n    E --> F[\"Locate session source\"]\n    F --> G[\"Read transcript records\"]\n    G --> H[\"Apply capture cursor\"]\n    H --> I[\"Normalize records\"]\n    I --> J[\"Plan GitMeta writes\"]\n    J --> K{\"dry run?\"}\n    K -->|\"yes\"| L[\"Return command output\"]\n    K -->|\"no\"| M[\"Write GitMeta local state\"]\n    M --> P[\"Return command output\"]\n```\n\n## Target Resolution\n\nTarget resolution should be conservative.\n\nFor the POC:\n\n1. Use the explicit `--target` value when present.\n2. Otherwise use `project`.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:15:26.616Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}